Task 2.a : What is the complete instruction? Look up the manual and
fill the instruction bellow. Then compile and execute.

complete instruction:
mrc p15, 0, &lt;Rt&gt;, c1, c1, 0
compile

try to install this kernel module

A segmentation fault occurs.

Task 2.b : Why the segmentation fault occurs?

The segmentation fault occurs because the kernel module executes a
privileged instruction that is not allowed in the current processor
mode.
Specifically, the inline assembly instruction
mrc p15, 0, &lt;Rt&gt;, c1, c1, 0
tries to access the Secure Configuration Register (SCR), which
belongs to the secure world.
However, the Linux kernel runs in the non-secure world at
EL1.
